records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
COUNT 50; 1ST DEGREE SEXUAL ASSAULT OF CHILD (UNDER AGE 12)  
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of fifty (50) years. That is thirty (30) years initial confinement followed by twenty (20) years extended supervision.

COUNTS 24, 47, 48, 49; 1ST DEGREE SEXUAL ASSAULT OF A CHILD (UNDER AGE 13)  
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of thirty-five (35) years.  That is fifteen (15) years initial confinement followed by twenty (20) years extended supervision, on each count, concurrent, but consecutive to the sentence imposed on count 50.

COUNT 23; POSSESS WITH INTENT TO DISTRIBUTE CHILD SEXUAL EXPLOITATION  
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of ten (10) years. That is five (5) years initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision, consecutive to all other sentences.

COUNTS 1-4, 6-10, 26-32, 51-64, 66, 67, 69 AND 71; POSSESS CHILD PORNOGRAPHY  
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison system for a total of ten (10) years.  That is five (5) years initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision, on each count, concurrent, but consecutive to all other sentences.

The Court also orders that the $500.00 surcharge for each image be imposed.

COUNTS 11-14, 16-20, 34-40; CHILD SEXUAL EXPLOITATION (VIDEOS/RECORDS) 
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of ten (10) years.  That is five (5) years initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision, on each count, concurrent, but consecutive to all other sentences.

COUNTS 22, 41, 42, 43, 44, 45 AND 46; CHILD SEXUAL EXPLOITATION (PRODUCE/PERFORM)  
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of ten (10) years. That is five (5) years initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision, on each count, concurrent, but consecutive to all other sentences.

The Court finds the defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.

The court orders credit of 840 days.

Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Pay court costs;
3) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
4) register as a sexual offender;
5) undergo sex offender treatment;
6) no contact with A.K.H. or anyone under the age of 18 unless approved by the agent;
7) no use or possession or any internet enabled devices.
